    "description": "If you're a passionate Radiologist with drive and ambition, Manipal Hospitals Asia Pacific Associates in Surat is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Manipal Hospitals Asia Pacific Associates:\nManipal Hospitals Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Referral bonus program\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Surat, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Manipal Hospitals Asia Pacific Associates!",
